claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Excerpt of a clinical document showing text and footnotes defining vaccine abbreviations (e.g., RIV4: Flublok; SD-IIV4: standard-dose influenza vaccines) and reporting vaccine effectiveness (VE) data for different age and risk groups The image only defines vaccine abbreviations and presents VE results; it contains no information about HA antigen content or immunogenicity, so it does not support the claim
